   type=\"button\"\n  1703→            variant=\"muatparts-primary-secondary\"\n  1704→            className=\"h-8 w-[129px] rounded-[20px] border-[#176CF7] px-6 py-[7px] text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#176CF7]\"\n  1705→            onClick={onBack}\n  1706→          >\n  1707→            Sebelumnya\n  1708→          </Button>\n  1709→          {profile?.permissions?.booleanPermissions?.VENDOR_DOMESTIK?.APPROVE && (\n  1710→            <Button\n  1711→              type=\"submit\"\n  1712→              variant=\"muatparts-primary\"\n  1713→              className=\"h-8 w-[97px] rounded-[20px] bg-[#176CF7] px-6 py-[7px] text-[14px] font-semibold text-white\"\n  1714→              disabled={isSubmitting}\n  1715→            >\n  1716→              {isSubmitting ? \"Menyimpan...\" : \"Simpan\"}\n  1717→            </Button>\n  1718→          )}\n  1719→        </div>\n  1720→      </form>\n  1721→    </>\n  1722→  );\n  1723→};\n  1724→\n  1725→export default FormKontrak;\n  1726→```\n  1727→\n  1728→### Phase 5: Routing and Navigation Updates\n  1729→\n  1730→#### 5.1 Update URL Routing\n  1731→\n  1732→**File**: `src/app/vendor-domestik/verifikasi/[id]/page.tsx` (new file)\n  1733→\n  1734→```typescript\n  1735→import VerifikasiVendorDomestik from \"@/container/VerifikasiVendorDomestik/VerifikasiVendorDomestik\";\n  1736→\n  1737→const VerifikasiVendorDomestikPage = () => {\n  1738→  return <VerifikasiVendorDomestik />;\n  1739→};\n  1740→\n  1741→export default VerifikasiVendorDomestikPage;\n  1742→```\n  1743→\n  1744→#### 5.2 Update Navigation Links\n  1745→\n  1746→Update any links pointing to the domestic vendor registration to point to the verification workflow:\n  1747→\n  1748→```typescript\n  1749→// Update navigation from:\n  1750→/vendor-domestik/register\n  1751→\n  1752→// To verification workflow:\n  1753→/vendor-domestik/verifikasi/[id]\n  1754→```\n  1755→\n  1756→### Phase 6: Testing and Validation\n  1757→\n  1758→#### 6.1 Test Cases\n  1759→\n  1760→1. **Data Loading Tests**\n  1761→   - Verify vendor data loads correctly from API\n  1762→   - Test transformation from API to display format\n  1763→   - Validate error handling for missing vendors\n  1764→\n  1765→2. **Navigation Tests**\n  1766→   - Test breadcrumb navigation between steps\n  1767→   - Verify previous/next button functionality\n  1768→   - Test redirect on successful verification\n  1769→\n  1770→3. **Approval Workflow Tests**\n  1771→   - Test approve workflow with proper permission checks\n  1772→   - Test reject workflow with required rejection notes\n  1773→   - Validate API updates for both approval and rejection\n  1774→\n  1775→4. **Display Accuracy Tests**\n  1776→   - Verify all domestik-specific fields display correctly\n  1777→   - Test vendor type-specific brand field display\n  1778→   - Validate file upload display functionality\n  1779→\n  1780→5. **Permission Tests**\n  1781→   - Test approval section visibility with/without permissions\n  1782→   - Verify non-authorized users cannot approve/reject\n  1783→   - Test permission-based UI elements\n  1784→\n  1785→#### 6.2 Browser Testing Matrix\n  1786→\n  1787→| Browser | Data Loading | Form Display | Approval | Permissions |\n  1788→| ------- | ------------ | ------------ | -------- | ----------- |\n  1789→| Chrome  | ✅           | ✅           | ✅       | ✅          |\n  1790→| Firefox | ✅           | ✅           | ✅       | ✅          |\n  1791→| Safari  | ✅           | ✅           | ✅       | ✅          |\n  1792→| Edge    | ✅           | ✅           | ✅       | ✅          |\n  1793→\n  1794→#### 6.3 Device Testing\n  1795→\n  1796→- Desktop: Full functionality testing\n  1797→- Tablet: Responsive layout verification\n  1798→- Mobile: Touch interface and scroll behavior\n  1799→\n  1800→---\n  1801→\n  1802→## 🚀 Deployment Checklist\n  1803→\n  1804→### Pre-Deployment\n  1805→\n  1806→- [ ] All API services created and tested\n  1807→- [ ] Type definitions updated and validated\n  1808→- [ ] Form components transformed to read-only\n  1809→- [ ] Permission system implemented\n  1810→- [ ] Error handling added to all components\n  1811→- [ ] Browser compatibility tested\n  1812→- [ ] Mobile responsiveness verified\n  1813→\n  1814→### Post-Deployment\n  1815→\n  1816→- [ ] Monitor API error rates\n  1817→- [ ] Check user permission functionality\n  1818→- [ ] Verify vendor data display accuracy\n  1819→- [ ] Test approval/rejection workflows in production\n  1820→- [ ] Collect user feedback on workflow changes\n  1821→\n  1822→---\n  1823→\n  1824→## 📊 Success Metrics\n  1825→\n  1826→### Technical Metrics\n  1827→\n  1828→- **Page Load Time**: < 3 seconds for vendor data loading\n  1829→- **API Response Time**: < 1 second for fetch and update operations\n  1830→- **Error Rate**: < 1% for all API calls\n  1831→- **Browser Compatibility**: 100% across supported browsers\n  1832→\n  1833→### User Experience Metrics\n  1834→\n  1835→- **Task Completion Rate**: > 95% for verification workflow\n  1836→- **Time to Complete**: < 5 minutes per vendor verification\n  1837→- **User Satisfaction**: > 4.5/5 for workflow simplicity\n  1838→- **Error Rate**: < 2% for user interactions\n  1839→\n  1840→---\n  1841→\n  1842→## 🔧 Maintenance Considerations\n  1843→\n  1844→### Ongoing Maintenance\n  1845→\n  1846→- Monitor API performance and error rates\n  1847→- Keep permission systems updated with role changes\n  1848→- Maintain browser compatibility with new releases\n  1849→- Update type definitions as API contracts evolve\n  1850→\n  1851→### Future Enhancements\n  1852→\n  1853→- Add bulk approval functionality\n  1854→- Implement advanced filtering and search\n  1855→- Add vendor status change notifications\n  1856→- Create audit trail for all verification actions\n  1857→\n  1858→---\n  1859→\n  1860→## 📚 Documentation Updates\n  1861→\n  1862→### Developer Documentation\n  1863→\n  1864→- Update API service documentation\n  1865→- Document transformation functions\n  1866→- Create troubleshooting guide for common issues\n  1867→- Update deployment procedures\n  1868→\n  1869→### User Documentation\n  1870→\n  1871→- Create user guide for verification workflow\n  1872→- Document permission requirements\n  1873→- Add screenshots of updated interface\n  1874→- Create FAQ for common verification scenarios\n  1875→\n  1876→---\n  1877→\n  1878→## ✅ Conversion Complete Checklist\n  1879→\n  1880→When this conversion is complete, the domestik verification system will:\n  1881→\n  1882→- [ ] **Load existing vendor data** from API using vendor ID from URL\n  1883→- [ ] **Display all information** in read-only format with domestik complexity preserved\n  1884→- [ ] **Maintain 4 vendor types** with their unique field requirements\n  1885→- [ ] **Provide navigation** between 3 steps like international version\n  1886→- [ ] **Include approval section** with permission-based access control\n  1887→- [ ] **Update vendor status** based on approval/rejection decisions\n  1888→- [ ] **Handle errors gracefully** with user-friendly messages\n  1889→- [ ] **Redirect appropriately** after successful verification\n  1890→- [ ] **Match international workflow** simplicity while maintaining domestik requirements\n  1891→\n  1892→This conversion transforms the domestik system from a complex registration form into a streamlined verification workflow while preserving all the unique requirements and field complexity that distinguishes domestic vendors from international ones.\n  1893→\n  1894→\n  1895→... (-107 more lines truncated)","metadata":{"truncated":true,"lineCount":1893,"filePath":"conversion-plan.md","preview":false}}}}

